cs.NE, cs.Optics, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.MM

The paper discusses the use of trainable media for neural network style training, which falls under the category of machine learning and optimization (cs.NE). The paper also focuses on the interaction between waves and a trainable medium, which suggests a potential application in optics (cs.Optics). The use of waves and propagation also suggests a potential application in signal processing (cs.SI) and wave propagation (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses a potential way to build such a device in an integrated photonics chip, which suggests a potential application in multimedia (cs.MM).
